<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4951772>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 6. 1–4. Ptilorhynchia aff. plumasensis Crickmay, USGS Mesozoic Locality 32032 (=80Ace119), Karluk Quadrangle, Alaska, Shelikof Formation, Callovian, Middle Jurassic, dorsal, ventral, lateral, and anterior views. 5–8. Ptilorhynchia jeletzkyi Owen, USGS Mesozoic locality 14496, co–occurs with Buchia mosquensis (von Buch), probably Naknek series, Kimmeridgian–Tithonian(?), Upper Jurassic, McCarthy Quadrangle, Alaska. Collector, Fred H. Moffit, 1928. Dorsal, ventral, lateral, and anterior views.9–17. Ptilorhynchia obscuricostata Dagys. 9–12. PMO 224.880, seep 9, dorsal, ventral, lateral, and anterior views. 13–17. PMO 224.881, seep 9, dorsal, ventral, lateral, anterior and posterior views. Scale bar = 1 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4951772/files/figure.png" .

